RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 1 4F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 7200. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHENUDON'T KNOW Broke sharply, quickly and effortlessly made way to lead by crossing over to the two path, was never challenged from that point and always looked a winner. MR BUG Z Chased blitzing leader well off the rail, second best. CLASSIC CALIFORNIA Cut across inside three rivals fifty yards out of the gate and impeded BELLA VINO greatly, moved up slightly between rivals in the move up of the backstretch, swung wide for the stretch, gained late. WEST COAST ANDY Moved up shortly after the break to challenge for second with inside rival, chased in the four path, faded late. IGO Tracked off the pace throughout, never did enough to advance. FACE OF GRACE Broke inwards greatly, taken back after the awkward start and settled well off the pace, never had run. BELLA VINO Away a touch slow, taken out by outside rival cutting across as they passed the backstretch gap and was unable to threaten from that point. DYNAMIC WOMAN Pinched at the start by outside rival and inside rival holding lane, trailed throughout following rough break, never a factor. A STEWARDS INQUIRY AND RIDERS OBJECTION WAS LODGED INTO THE START OF THE RACE. IT WAS DETERMINED #4 CLASSIC CALIFORNIA IMPEDED #1 BELLA VINO TO A LEVEL THAT WOULD AFFECT HER BEST PLACING. #4 CLASSIC CALIFORNIA WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FOURTH TO SEVENTH PLACE.

ENTRY.NAME: Bella Vino
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Away touch slow, taken out by outs rival, never factored after

ENTRY.NAME: Dynamic Woman
ENTRY.COMMENT: Pinched break, trailed throughout, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Face of Grace
ENTRY.COMMENT: Broke inwards heavily, well off pace, never had run

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Classic California
ENTRY.COMMENT: Cut across ins sharply after break, adv throughout, swung wide

ENTRY.NAME: Mr Bug Z
ENTRY.COMMENT: Chased leader well off rail, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: West Coast Andy
ENTRY.COMMENT: Moved up shortly after the start to chllng, faded late

ENTRY.NAME: Igo
ENTRY.COMMENT: Tracked throughout, never advanced

ENTRY.NAME: Whenudon't Know
ENTRY.COMMENT: Brk sharply, quickly crossed to two path, was never challenged

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 2 4F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2022 - 2023. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BAPTISM Broke on top and led in three path opening stages before conceding lead to rail rival at the five-sixteenths pole, stayed a threat throughout turn and re-engaged at the eighth pole outside while chasing rival, wore down opponent in final strides. SONGOFTHEDESERT Hustled along rail and vied in line of three before emerging with lead at the five-sixteenths pole, got away from quartet of foes at three-sixteenths pole while continuing to travel along rail, fought gamely throughout stretch but was nailed on the line. CANT DO THE DANSE Broke in frame and was between battling leaders early, ultimately backed out and dropped to the rail second flight behind leading duo, called upon into the lane along inside but ran evenly when asked. EPIC DRAMA Set up second flight in touch with leaders between horses up the backstretch, got out slightly into the turn while leaning on outside foe, never threatened down stretch. LIVE A GOOD LIFE Set up shop three wide backstretch travelling in line of two and then three when rival dropped into line at the five-sixteenths pole, was carried out two paths rounding the turn by inside rival, flattened out down the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Songofthedesert
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Hustled, snuck up rail to lead 5/16, got away 3/16, naild on line

ENTRY.NAME: Cant Do the Danse
ENTRY.OWNER: Pallanes, Alan J. and Arnold, Pete
ENTRY.COMMENT: Btwn early, drop to rail behind two leaders, evenly when asked

ENTRY.NAME: Baptism
ENTRY.COMMENT: Broke on top, conceded lead 5/16, reengaged 1/8 outs, in time

ENTRY.NAME: Epic Drama
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2nd flight in touch between 5/16, asked 3/16, got out on turn

ENTRY.NAME: Live a Good Life
ENTRY.OWNER: King Danna King Chase and Messing Michael
ENTRY.COMMENT: Three wide backside and into turn, carried wider bend, flattened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 8100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 11. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: A GEM IS A GEM Vied along rail from the break with outside foe, moved to a narrow lead at the seven-sixteenths pole and controlled all the way home to victory. ROYAL TAP Vied outside rival throughout, was a clear second into the far turn but still in place to threaten, battled while chasing nagging inner foe, never found enough to win. FIRST COUNT Stalked three wide from the break while well in touch of leaders, never improved throughout, never weakened throughout. BREXTON Taken back last immediately following the start, sat steady until commencing a three wide bid at the five-sixteenths pole, while the mild move was apparent it was stymied by a commanding top duo throughout. ROLL OUT Settled in back half along the two path opening stages, began move at the three-eighths pole in the two path, showed a very unimpressionable and slim gain down the stretch. ZENMAGIC Tracked off the early foot on the rail, called upon at the five-sixteenths pole, showed no response, was taken care of to the wire.

ENTRY.NAME: A Gem Is a Gem
ENTRY.COMMENT: Vied rail, narrow lead 7/16ths, controlled all the way home

ENTRY.COMMENT: Tracked off pace rail, asked 5/16ths, no response, taken care of

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 82. Allowance Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG CITY BANE Inside of foes well off flying leader opening stages, began to advance along the rail starting at the three-eights pole and steadily improved making his way into the stretch, surged down the lane and got up in dying frames. TIGER BY HIS TAIL Blitzed to the lead and opened up a healthy advantage on the competition, showed signs of weariness at the three-sixteenths pole and drifted a few paths making way into stretch at the eighth pole, fought while tiring yet still nipped at the wire. ROCKED Tracked in the second flight inside of rival, moved at the five-sixteenths pole along the three path, rallied on the wrong lead down the center of the stretch, not enough. NORTHERN QUEST Trailed inside, showed mild improve past tiring foes, never a menace. LINEMANS CHECK Sat well off the pace in the middle of the pack striding along in the fourth lane, asked at multiple stages but yielded no response. AUTISM SAVANT Traveled well off the rail and well off the pace throughout, maintained wide path of travel throughout, never a threat. KATZUMOTO Tracked in the second flight along the rail and inside a foe, after showing brief speed faded throughout.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Allowance Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALEX'S GIRL Broke very alertly and fired to lead comfortably, maintained strong motion up backstretch on top, commanded into the lane, held lone challenger at bay in final sixteenth. HUGHIE'S HOLIDAY Stalked in three path early on, commenced three wide bid on the far turn, pursued leader into the lane but was unable to run her down. PRINCESS SUGEITH Pressed along the two path, asked at the three-sixteenths pole to threaten, faded down stretch. KIND BUT SHE LIES Stumbled to knees at start, asked to keep pace and eventually showed gain along the backside in the four path, flattened out when the running got going. PREDETERMINATION Was far back throughout and passed one tiring foe. MEXICAN DREAM Tucked in pocket along rail just behind the leader, advanced a few lengths into the first turn, asked throughout to stay engaged, ultimately gave in at the quarter pole and was eased home.
